I'd like to make some recommendations to mitigate potential fatiguing of these semi-threadly happenings. Take them with a grain of salt.

>Take 5
Post these once or twice a week, saving at least one of them for the weekend to liven things up in less active times.
>History
Post these once every 5 years, doing high-level summaries of these periods rather than stretching for content for individual years. It would give you more room to create a relevant prompt as well.
>Thread Recaps
Trim the fat as best as you can. If everything's important, nothing is. Recommend using a structure like the following:

<Thread #XXXX>

>>XXXXXXXX

>New art (this can be uploaded as part of the post):

>>XXXXXXXX

>>XXXXXXXX

I'd do that as a circuit
set of JJ, set of SU, etc
Start at 8-10 reps, move to harder variations once you hit 20-30 reps. Move fast and you'll eventually find the balance you need to work strength/power & endurance/cardio

Depending on your weight, fitness level & build it might work as something to build up to.
